{"Title": "Experimental design and analysis and their reporting II: updated and simplified guidance for authors and peer reviewers", "Year": 2018, "Source": "Br. J. Pharmacol.", "Volume": "175", "Issue": 7, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 987, "PageEnd": 993, "CitedBy": 531, "DOI": "10.1111/bph.14153", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85043393318&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2018 The British Pharmacological SocietyThis article updates the guidance published in 2015 for authors submitting papers to British Journal of Pharmacology (Curtis et al., 2015) and is intended to provide the rubric for peer review. Thus, it is directed towards authors, reviewers and editors. Explanations for many of the requirements were outlined previously and are not restated here. The new guidelines are intended to replace those published previously. The guidelines have been simplified for ease of understanding by authors, to make it more straightforward for peer reviewers to check compliance and to facilitate the curation of the journal's efforts to improve standards.", "AuthorKeywords": null, "IndexKeywords": ["Peer Review, Research", "Periodicals as Topic", "Research Design", "Research Report"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 1, "EID": "2-s2.0-85043393318", "SubjectAreas": [["Pharmacology", "PHAR", "3004"]], "AuthorData": {"18834149300": {"Name": "Curtis M.J.", "AuthorID": "18834149300", "AffiliationID": "60011520", "AffiliationName": "Kings College London"}, "56905914300": {"Name": "Alexander S.", "AuthorID": "56905914300", "AffiliationID": "60015138", "AffiliationName": "University of Nottingham"}, "7006917147": {"Name": "Cirino G.", "AuthorID": "7006917147", "AffiliationID": "60017293", "AffiliationName": "University of Naples"}, "55382764100": {"Name": "Izzo A.A.", "AuthorID": "55382764100", "AffiliationID": "60017293", "AffiliationName": "University of Naples"}, "7102949728": {"Name": "Docherty J.R.", "A